g a permanently ‘leaner’ state. The book assesses the character of this shift in thinking as well as the viability of these efforts to shrink the state and the parallel attempts in the US to cut federal government spending through mechanisms such as the budget sequester.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aConservatismx21st centuryxGreat Britain. 0aConservatismx21st centuryxUnited States. 0aConservatismzGreat Britainy21st century. 0aConservatismzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aConservatism. 0aGlobal Financial Crisis, 2008-2009. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh  aAusterity.  aConservatism.  aIntercurrence.  aNeoliberalism.  aRetrenchment.  aState restructuring.1 aAshbee, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499223140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784992231423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784992231/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles